  adversarial:
    "The apology-only failure: getting the firewall lifted with a hotfix and goodwill — the class is untouched, the next capability stampedes a different system, and the SECOND blame thread hardens into standing hostility toward the whole fleet (014's wall, now with receipts). The infrastructure reflex: 'the CRM should scale up' — sometimes true (see the falsifier), always the wrong opening move; demanding capacity from the system you just stampeded is how integration partners become enemies. The gate-skip: fixing this integration beautifully and leaving the ship process unchanged — the load review line is the whole class fix; without it you've patched one stampede and scheduled the rest.",
